{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-20217/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-20217"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["2:02:17"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["full shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["eye-level"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, handheld, tracking"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["three shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A trio of people stand and sit around a park bench with a stroller."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20217/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-20217","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20217/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-20217"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20217/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20217/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20217/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20217/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20217/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20217/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20217/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20217/canvas/1/84059e3f-41c8-454b-a376-23f0e706453a","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T14:34:16.173Z","creator":"Ada ","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Reynolds here wears his trademark pink socks, along with a new similarly colored ascot. Alma’s presence brings new colors into his life, literally and figuratively.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20217/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:771.5086722488038,372.5889653110047,137.92015550239228,469.7884270334927"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20217/canvas/1/d55cfdc2-675a-4673-b92d-2b831fe42a63","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T14:34:38.761Z","creator":"Ada ","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>During their first meeting, Reynolds asks whether Alma will be able to remember his order at the restaurant, and without hesitation, she answers, “Yes.” In this narration, Alma says that she can predict the future and see how everything in their life together has settled. In one sense, she is claiming narrative control over their story together, and this epilogue is a visual representation of that power. Reynolds has continually tried to maintain control in their relationship, but ultimately, if she is the one who gets to tell the story, the power lies with her.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20217/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:32.183581480583996,40.71591465362573,313.4533802419039,212.42254228417323"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20217/canvas/1/106aa021-4955-43f2-9633-63cc475717ce","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T14:35:00.240Z","creator":"Ada ","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>According to first assistant camera operator Erik Brown, there were scenes shot involving Reynolds visiting his “ex-wives” and delivering fabrics to them for his children to play with (Lux Lighting, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW202126012 BCX4\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zpgyq9VhOIA\"><u>Lighting Phantom Thread Q&amp;A</u></a>”).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-20217/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:32.69587320574169,285.11214114832535,313.9428827751194,216.46830143540666"}}}]}]}]}